definition: horse/CL:匹[pi3]/horse or cavalry piece in Chinese chess/knight in Western chess
surname Ma/abbr. for Malaysia 馬來西亞|马来西亚[Ma3 lai2 xi1 ya4]
he or him/(used for either sex when the sex is unknown or unimportant)/(used before sb's name for emphasis)/(used as a meaningless mock object)/other/another

sentences.english: In 1814, Malta became a part of the British Empire.

sentences.english: VALLETTA, Malta – How things have changed.
The Republic of Malta is a small and densely-populated island nation in southern Europe.

sentences.english: 1964 - Malta becomes independent from the United Kingdom.

sentences.english: No Maltese athlete has won an Olympic medal to date.

sentences.english: And when they were escaped, then they knew that the island was called Melita.

sentences.english: The Maltese nobility was established during this period.

sentences.english: Support for the Yes vote has fallen sharply according to a latest survey of Malta.
